WEBVTT

00:00:00.266 --> 00:00:02.106
(Child actors were accompanied by a guardian...)

00:00:02.106 --> 00:00:03.536
(and filmed in a safe, supervised environment.)

00:00:04.676 --> 00:00:07.006
Are you the only one working? I work, too.

00:00:07.106 --> 00:00:08.616
I'm exhausted, too.

00:00:08.876 --> 00:00:11.376
Please. For the pathetic amount you make?

00:00:11.446 --> 00:00:15.016
You dump the housework and our kid on Mom and do whatever you want.

00:00:15.086 --> 00:00:16.256
Let's just drop it.

00:00:16.616 --> 00:00:19.386
I was a fool to marry someone like you.

00:00:19.456 --> 00:00:23.096
Fine, then let's call it quits. Let's get a divorce. Right now!

00:00:25.626 --> 00:00:27.326
Wow, that's really intense.

00:00:27.696 --> 00:00:29.966
Dr. Han Seong Mi, what's your take on that?

00:00:30.436 --> 00:00:33.506
Yes. According to the research of Dr. John Gottman,

00:00:33.566 --> 00:00:35.736
a world-renowned couples therapist,

00:00:36.276 --> 00:00:39.206
criticism, contempt, defensiveness, and stonewalling...

00:00:39.476 --> 00:00:43.346
are four major factors that destroy a relationship.

00:00:44.516 --> 00:00:46.716
Unfortunately, the couple we just saw...

00:00:46.786 --> 00:00:49.686
is engaging in these kinds of dysfunctional communication habits.

00:00:50.286 --> 00:00:53.656
So that's why the more they talk, the more emotional they get,

00:00:53.786 --> 00:00:55.896
and the deeper their conflict becomes.

00:00:56.696 --> 00:01:00.896
In that case, what's the solution for this family?

00:01:01.226 --> 00:01:05.336
What this family needs most of all is to repair their relationship.

00:01:06.206 --> 00:01:09.376
And that starts with love.

00:01:10.036 --> 00:01:12.106
To heal a relationship hardened by past wounds,

00:01:12.446 --> 00:01:15.216
and to change the way they feel through their words and actions,

00:01:15.716 --> 00:01:18.616
love must always be at the center of it all.

00:01:19.986 --> 00:01:21.386
That is why today, for this couple,

00:01:22.656 --> 00:01:24.656
I am prescribing love.

00:01:26.456 --> 00:01:28.596
(Recipe for Love)

00:01:28.996 --> 00:01:30.756
(Jin Se Yun, Park Ki Woong)

00:01:32.896 --> 00:01:34.826
(Kim Seung Soo, Yoo Ho Jeong)

00:01:36.766 --> 00:01:38.566
(Kim Hyeong Mook, So E Hyun)

00:01:41.036 --> 00:01:43.476
(Kim Mi Sook, Joo Jin Mo)

00:01:44.176 --> 00:01:46.576
(Choi Dae Chul, Jo Mee Ryung)

00:01:46.646 --> 00:01:48.516
(Han Seung Won, Kang Byeol, Kim Sun Bin, Yoon Seo Ah)

00:01:48.576 --> 00:01:50.576
(Jin Yong Wook, Hong Jin Ki, Jo Yi Hyeon, Kim Min Ah)

00:01:50.646 --> 00:01:53.116
(Kim Jong Hoon, Jung Ye Seo, Cha Seung Joo, Park Jeong Gon)

00:01:53.186 --> 00:01:58.316
(Recipe for Love)

00:01:58.826 --> 00:02:00.626
(Episode 1)

00:02:05.326 --> 00:02:06.326
You're here.

00:02:06.796 --> 00:02:07.896
I'm not late.

00:02:08.126 --> 00:02:11.066
I know. I figured it was about time, so I came out to greet you.

00:02:11.696 --> 00:02:13.666
Look at Mr. Big Shot coming out to greet me.

00:02:14.066 --> 00:02:15.536
What is it? What do you need?

00:02:16.206 --> 00:02:17.306
Come, this way.

00:02:17.906 --> 00:02:21.346
Let's talk at dinner after filming. It's my treat for your birthday.

00:02:21.676 --> 00:02:25.446
- You still remember my birthday? - Of course. You're my first love.

00:02:26.046 --> 00:02:27.646
I'll book a table at your favorite crab place.

00:02:27.916 --> 00:02:30.956
No, thanks. It's my birthday. I should spend it with my family.

00:02:31.316 --> 00:02:32.486
If it's urgent, just tell me now.

00:02:35.856 --> 00:02:39.496
Let's do a new show. Your own solo show.

00:02:40.296 --> 00:02:41.466
I don't think I can.

00:02:41.766 --> 00:02:43.966
My clinic schedule is way too packed.

00:02:44.496 --> 00:02:45.806
I know I was scraping by...

00:02:45.806 --> 00:02:47.936
before my college buddy, a broadcasting director,

00:02:48.006 --> 00:02:49.736
gave me a shot, and I'm grateful to be this busy,

00:02:50.106 --> 00:02:51.576
but I have a day job to get back to.

00:02:52.646 --> 00:02:54.746
All right. Let me know if you change your mind. Anytime.

00:02:56.146 --> 00:02:59.446
"Go Myung Hwan's Book Talk." Today's guest...

00:02:59.886 --> 00:03:03.716
is someone our viewers have been dying to meet.

00:03:04.086 --> 00:03:08.626
She's the author of the bestseller, "Recipe for Love,"

00:03:08.956 --> 00:03:13.926
the love guru who prescribes love to all of Korea's troubled families,

00:03:14.296 --> 00:03:18.636
and a board-certified psychiatrist, Dr. Han Seong Mi.

00:03:19.036 --> 00:03:20.666
Welcome.

00:03:21.706 --> 00:03:24.076
- Welcome. - Hello.

00:03:24.136 --> 00:03:25.476
- Hello. - Hello.

00:03:32.816 --> 00:03:36.386
Now, I'd like to ask a more personal question.

00:03:36.616 --> 00:03:39.786
In fact, the number one thing our viewers want to know...

00:03:40.126 --> 00:03:44.026
is about your family life.

00:03:44.126 --> 00:03:45.296
Oh, right.

00:03:45.726 --> 00:03:47.566
According to my notes here,

00:03:47.626 --> 00:03:50.936
you and three generations of your family...

00:03:51.036 --> 00:03:55.106
- live in Onjeong. Right? - Yes, that's right.

00:03:55.376 --> 00:03:57.906
I live with my mother-in-law, my children who still live at home,

00:03:57.976 --> 00:04:00.346
and my brother-in-law and his wife as well.

00:04:00.446 --> 00:04:03.276
Wow, that's a real multigenerational household.

00:04:03.516 --> 00:04:05.946
Any trouble with your mother-in-law?

00:04:06.046 --> 00:04:10.086
- None whatsoever. That's a fact. - Wow, really?

00:04:10.556 --> 00:04:15.186
The person I look up to the most is my mother-in-law.

00:04:15.426 --> 00:04:18.296
Wow, what's she like?

00:04:18.726 --> 00:04:21.196
For starters, she's absolutely beautiful.

00:04:21.726 --> 00:04:25.236
She takes such great care of herself that whenever we go out together,

00:04:25.296 --> 00:04:27.836
- people ask if we're sisters. - Oh, my.

00:04:28.166 --> 00:04:31.976
And on top of that, she waltzes every morning.

00:04:32.176 --> 00:04:34.476
Excuse me? She waltzes?

00:04:36.176 --> 00:04:40.486
Yes. She and my father-in-law used to waltz when they were young,

00:04:40.786 --> 00:04:45.286
and she still does it every single day for exercise.

00:04:51.996 --> 00:04:56.236
In fact, she's the only reason I'm able to have a career.

00:05:01.866 --> 00:05:04.936
Everyone, time to eat!

00:05:06.576 --> 00:05:10.716
As I'm busy, she's raised our kids as if they were her own,

00:05:11.046 --> 00:05:15.086
and she manages our huge household perfectly, all by herself.

00:05:15.146 --> 00:05:16.156
- Eat up. - This looks delicious!

00:05:16.216 --> 00:05:20.786
My mother-in-law is always the steady center of our family.

00:05:20.986 --> 00:05:23.126
She's the rock that holds us all together.

00:05:25.126 --> 00:05:28.126
Is your mother-in-law a full-time homemaker?

00:05:28.496 --> 00:05:31.036
No, she's a pharmacist.

00:05:31.196 --> 00:05:33.536
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:05:33.606 --> 00:05:35.006
She works with my husband, a doctor,

00:05:35.006 --> 00:05:36.876
and my brother-in-law, a physical therapist.

00:05:36.936 --> 00:05:39.776
- They're all in the same building. - Thank you.

00:05:39.846 --> 00:05:41.706
- Take care. - Thanks.

00:05:41.906 --> 00:05:44.376
I see.

00:05:44.846 --> 00:05:49.656
So your husband's a doctor. His late grandfather, his father...

00:05:49.716 --> 00:05:51.456
and... Wait.

00:05:51.856 --> 00:05:54.456
Your two children also went to med school?

00:05:55.256 --> 00:05:56.256
Yes.

00:05:56.356 --> 00:06:00.326
And your husband is an internist... Hang on a second.

00:06:00.496 --> 00:06:03.266
Your face just lit up the second we mentioned your husband.

00:06:03.266 --> 00:06:05.266
- It did. - My gosh. Did it, really?

00:06:06.536 --> 00:06:08.666
What's your husband like?

00:06:10.706 --> 00:06:12.306
My husband...

00:06:13.146 --> 00:06:15.976
is a truly selfless and idealistic doctor.

00:06:16.516 --> 00:06:19.146
You'd be so surprised if you saw his clinic.

00:06:21.946 --> 00:06:24.216
- Hello. Good to see you. - Yes, hello.

00:06:25.626 --> 00:06:26.786
Hello, welcome.

00:06:26.856 --> 00:06:29.796
It feels less like a clinic and more like a local hangout.

00:06:32.826 --> 00:06:36.966
Try to bend it a little, like this. Oh, ouch...

00:06:37.496 --> 00:06:40.466
This must've hurt so much you couldn't get any sleep.

00:06:40.536 --> 00:06:42.906
- He's so down-to-earth and warm. - It really hurts.

00:06:43.376 --> 00:06:46.776
He treats his patients like family. No, actually...

00:06:46.846 --> 00:06:48.476
He treats them like his own best friends.

00:06:49.676 --> 00:06:53.546
- Just roll up your pant leg a bit. - Here, mix this with your rice.

00:06:54.046 --> 00:06:57.256
- Don't bring me things you sell. - Please.

00:06:57.586 --> 00:07:00.156
Doctor, you're the one who helped me walk again,

00:07:00.226 --> 00:07:02.756
and you even played matchmaker for my granddaughter.

00:07:02.856 --> 00:07:06.566
- Just a jar of fermented seafood. - Honestly.

00:07:07.296 --> 00:07:09.966
But yours is too good. I can't possibly say no...

00:07:10.136 --> 00:07:12.066
All right, thank you. I'll enjoy it.

00:07:12.866 --> 00:07:16.336
- Watch your step on the way out. - I will.

00:07:18.236 --> 00:07:21.106
Mr. Go! My goodness. What have you brought now?

00:07:21.176 --> 00:07:23.546
I told you. You shouldn't be carrying heavy things.

00:07:23.616 --> 00:07:25.416
It's some nabak kimchi.

00:07:26.286 --> 00:07:30.156
Your favorite. My daughter made it for you.

00:07:31.616 --> 00:07:35.126
Gosh, you know a meal isn't complete for me without this.

00:07:35.796 --> 00:07:37.926
- Oh, boy. - It's the best, right?

00:07:39.996 --> 00:07:44.896
- I really wish I could be on TV - And he's such a romantic.

00:07:45.906 --> 00:07:47.966
- Singing - He likes music therapy too,

00:07:47.966 --> 00:07:50.006
- And dancing - so he volunteers on weekends.

00:07:50.076 --> 00:07:54.176
- My pretty face - Oh, my.

00:07:54.476 --> 00:07:57.516
That's what made you fall for him and get married young.

00:07:57.576 --> 00:08:00.616
What about your children? You said they were med students.

00:08:00.686 --> 00:08:02.556
Go on and brag a little.

00:08:04.256 --> 00:08:08.486
Our son graduated from med school and is now studying for his boards.

00:08:09.096 --> 00:08:12.126
He'll take over his dad's practice and become a great doctor,

00:08:12.196 --> 00:08:15.566
making him the fourth generation of doctors in the family.

00:08:16.996 --> 00:08:19.536
Is your daughter a doctor, too?

00:08:19.836 --> 00:08:23.336
No. She earned her medical license,

00:08:23.406 --> 00:08:25.946
but she felt a different calling and is doing something else now.

00:08:26.006 --> 00:08:27.276
And what is it that she does?

00:08:28.306 --> 00:08:31.546
- Our daughter's a designer. - A designer?

00:08:31.846 --> 00:08:35.756
She says that in their own way, designers are healers, too.

00:08:36.516 --> 00:08:40.656
They help people's emotional health by creating clothes that suit them.

00:08:40.986 --> 00:08:43.756
A "fashion therapist," if you will.

00:08:44.256 --> 00:08:48.526
Wow. You really seem perfect. You even raised your kids so well.

00:08:49.236 --> 00:08:52.566
For everyone watching at home today, could you share your secret...

00:08:52.636 --> 00:08:56.036
- to raising such a perfect family? - Of course.

00:08:56.806 --> 00:09:01.046
First, we respect each other, and we don't bottle up our emotions.

00:09:01.646 --> 00:09:06.086
We've learned to communicate without blaming each other.

00:09:06.686 --> 00:09:10.086
My, I bet every family in Korea is envious of you.

00:09:10.156 --> 00:09:12.586
You're such a perfect, exemplary family.

00:09:22.396 --> 00:09:25.336
Where did everyone go? Lunch is almost over.

00:09:30.406 --> 00:09:31.406
You startled me!

00:09:32.006 --> 00:09:34.706
My goodness. What is all this?

00:09:34.806 --> 00:09:38.876
- Happy birthday, Dr. Han! - Happy birthday!

00:09:39.616 --> 00:09:42.286
Thanks. Thank you both.

00:09:44.416 --> 00:09:45.416
Hold on.

00:09:48.126 --> 00:09:50.156
Oh, it's my husband.

00:09:50.656 --> 00:09:53.996
He's calling for your birthday.

00:09:53.996 --> 00:09:56.366
- How sweet! - Oh, stop.

00:09:56.366 --> 00:09:58.536
We'll get ready for the afternoon appointments then.

00:09:58.536 --> 00:09:59.936
- All right. Thanks. - All right, then.

00:09:59.936 --> 00:10:01.766
- Of course, happy birthday! - Happy birthday!

00:10:04.206 --> 00:10:05.976
(So-called husband, Gong Jeong Han)

00:10:11.646 --> 00:10:12.646
What is it?

00:10:13.416 --> 00:10:15.046
Hey, you busy?

00:10:15.856 --> 00:10:16.856
Kind of. Why?

00:10:17.456 --> 00:10:18.616
Today...

00:10:19.526 --> 00:10:21.056
You know, today...

00:10:22.856 --> 00:10:24.196
What about today? What is it?

00:10:24.556 --> 00:10:27.526
Well, today... I was wondering if you...

00:10:28.366 --> 00:10:31.296
Spit it out. What?

00:10:31.696 --> 00:10:32.706
No, it's just...

00:10:33.706 --> 00:10:35.436
I was wondering if you could lend me some money.

00:10:36.606 --> 00:10:37.936
Figures.

00:10:39.706 --> 00:10:40.706
Hello?

00:10:41.676 --> 00:10:43.176
Is that why you called? For money?

00:10:43.776 --> 00:10:44.776
What else?

00:10:45.176 --> 00:10:46.786
You only call when you need something, don't you?

00:10:47.046 --> 00:10:50.116
- So, do you have money to lend me? - And where would I get the money?

00:10:51.016 --> 00:10:52.156
Fine, forget it.

00:10:52.956 --> 00:10:54.626
Wait, what is it this time?

00:10:55.686 --> 00:10:57.296
You just said you don't have any money.

00:10:57.556 --> 00:10:59.166
Just tell me. Now!

00:10:59.526 --> 00:11:03.066
The high-frequency thermotherapy and premium AI ultrasound machines.

00:11:03.696 --> 00:11:05.266
Are you behind on the payments?

00:11:05.336 --> 00:11:08.866
Yes. If I can't pay by month's end, they're going to repossess them.

00:11:08.936 --> 00:11:10.636
See?

00:11:11.336 --> 00:11:15.746
Why buy them in the first place? For your hole-in-the-wall clinic?

00:11:16.116 --> 00:11:18.916
You have no idea how amazing these are, do you?

00:11:19.146 --> 00:11:23.186
It has a deep-learning engine that automatically analyzes lesions.

00:11:23.256 --> 00:11:25.516
How often do you use it?

00:11:25.516 --> 00:11:27.926
You see patients with colds, sore knees, and backs.

00:11:28.086 --> 00:11:31.156
Why buy something you can't afford if you're barely going to use it?

00:11:31.256 --> 00:11:34.696
Hey, I saved Mr. Baek from the hardware shop with this!

00:11:36.996 --> 00:11:39.206
Fine, forget it. I'll figure it out myself.

00:11:39.566 --> 00:11:42.636
Figure it out how? How are you going to solve anything?

00:11:43.336 --> 00:11:45.576
Take out another loan? Go to a loan shark?

00:11:45.906 --> 00:11:47.906
Did you even pay your brother this month?

00:11:49.346 --> 00:11:53.516
Please, just take patients who are insured!

00:11:53.586 --> 00:11:55.486
And stop giving out free treatments.

00:11:55.786 --> 00:11:57.686
How can you always be thinking only of other people?

00:11:57.986 --> 00:12:01.356
Are you running a charity? When are you going to stop?

00:12:01.486 --> 00:12:03.756
We both know we're short on money, so please stop causing trouble.

00:12:04.096 --> 00:12:05.656
Hey, but let's be honest.

00:12:06.026 --> 00:12:09.496
You took every last penny we had to open your clinic in Seoul.

00:12:09.566 --> 00:12:11.196
That's why we're so broke in the first place.

00:12:11.336 --> 00:12:15.006
I knew you'd bring that up. Did I make that decision by myself?

00:12:15.066 --> 00:12:19.276
Besides, am I not paying it back? I'm making payments every month.

00:12:19.406 --> 00:12:23.716
Since you're on TV more often and seeing more patients,

00:12:23.946 --> 00:12:27.186
I thought you'd be making more money, so I called.

00:12:27.416 --> 00:12:29.916
Between the rent for the clinic and the rent for my studio,

00:12:29.986 --> 00:12:33.256
- I'm stretched thin, too. - All right, I get it.

00:12:35.726 --> 00:12:36.926
For now, just try to buy some time.

00:12:37.756 --> 00:12:40.096
I'll come down this weekend, and we can talk about it then.

00:12:40.696 --> 00:12:42.266
You're coming home this weekend?

00:12:43.536 --> 00:12:44.536
You don't want me to?

00:12:44.596 --> 00:12:49.506
No, it's just you haven't been home in two months. Why so suddenly?

00:12:49.706 --> 00:12:52.706
Grandfather's memorial service is this week.

00:12:53.076 --> 00:12:54.476
Oh, right. The service.

00:12:54.776 --> 00:12:58.676
You only care about other people. You couldn't care less about home.

00:12:59.186 --> 00:13:01.316
Hello. Yes. I have to go.

00:13:01.616 --> 00:13:02.686
Hello...

00:13:10.396 --> 00:13:13.396
Love must always be at the center of it all.

00:13:14.496 --> 00:13:16.196
That is why today, for this couple,

00:13:17.266 --> 00:13:19.436
I am prescribing love.

00:13:20.136 --> 00:13:22.136
Love... What a joke.

00:13:28.246 --> 00:13:30.046
(Song Jae Geun)

00:13:30.876 --> 00:13:33.986
So, have you decided to give it a shot, Doctor?

00:13:34.386 --> 00:13:37.416
Yes. I talked it over with my husband,

00:13:37.756 --> 00:13:39.856
and he thought I should give it a shot.

00:13:40.756 --> 00:13:44.296
And since you're saying I'm needed, I'd like to be helpful if I can.

00:13:45.756 --> 00:13:48.466
Great. You're a true doctor couple, just as I thought.

00:13:49.196 --> 00:13:54.036
- Great decision. Thank you. - But I do have one question.

00:13:55.136 --> 00:13:59.406
Hosting a show under my own name is different from being a panelist.

00:14:00.046 --> 00:14:03.216
I was wondering about the fee and payment structure.

00:14:04.116 --> 00:14:05.216
Here.

00:14:06.646 --> 00:14:10.086
Wow, the rice is perfect today. Who made it?

00:14:10.416 --> 00:14:14.686
Yong Tae's grandmother did. Jeong Ah brought the greens.

00:14:14.956 --> 00:14:18.096
- We have nabak kimchi and seafood. - Oh, my.

00:14:18.156 --> 00:14:21.626
Oh, yes! Nabak kimchi from Mr. Go. It's the absolute best!

00:14:21.926 --> 00:14:24.296
Oh, Mom. About Mr. Go...

00:14:24.866 --> 00:14:25.936
He picked up his medicine, right?

00:14:26.006 --> 00:14:30.706
Yes. But you said he needed to make a hospital appointment? Why?

00:14:31.006 --> 00:14:33.306
I'm just a little worried about a potential heart attack.

00:14:33.876 --> 00:14:37.376
Oh, right. Ju Ah's mom is coming home this weekend.

00:14:37.776 --> 00:14:40.686
My gosh, you actually called her?

00:14:41.516 --> 00:14:44.286
What's the occasion? I didn't even have to remind you.

00:14:44.786 --> 00:14:45.786
Remind me of what?

00:14:46.326 --> 00:14:48.126
It's her birthday today.

00:14:49.826 --> 00:14:52.156
It's her birthday today?

00:14:52.596 --> 00:14:55.326
- You called her without knowing? - Of course, he didn't know.

00:14:56.436 --> 00:14:58.066
Then why did you call?

00:14:58.996 --> 00:15:00.606
Well, I just...

00:15:01.706 --> 00:15:02.806
Why do you think?

00:15:03.936 --> 00:15:06.106
Don't tell me you asked her for money.

00:15:07.306 --> 00:15:11.216
I can't believe this kid... I told you I'd take care of it.

00:15:11.746 --> 00:15:14.546
Why would you bother her with a call like that?

00:15:15.116 --> 00:15:18.086
How would you handle it, Mom? Where would you get the money?

00:15:18.456 --> 00:15:20.856
She said we'll talk again at this weekend's memorial service.

00:15:20.926 --> 00:15:23.896
She's so busy. Why would she come for the service? I can do it myself.

00:15:23.956 --> 00:15:27.166
Please, Mom. If she doesn't show up, you know Uncle will make a scene.

00:15:27.666 --> 00:15:30.666
Mr. Gong! If you take all that, what are we supposed to eat?

00:15:31.166 --> 00:15:33.966
What? Come on, there's plenty here.

00:15:34.236 --> 00:15:36.076
I'm taking some for Hui Gyeong.

00:15:36.236 --> 00:15:39.376
She's at home. She can feed herself. Why do you dote on her so much?

00:15:39.446 --> 00:15:41.076
Hey, we're still in our honeymoon phase.

00:15:41.076 --> 00:15:43.216
What are you talking about? You've been married for five years.

00:15:43.416 --> 00:15:47.246
You're still newlyweds with no kids. Legally, it lasts for seven years.

00:15:47.846 --> 00:15:52.786
Housing, tax breaks, and loans... All of it extends to seven years.

00:15:52.926 --> 00:15:55.356
Sure, whatever. Must be nice to be so lovey-dovey.

00:15:56.096 --> 00:16:00.266
I guess one marriage has to go well. Dr. Gong's marriage is struggling.

00:16:01.866 --> 00:16:04.136
I'm sorry. I don't know what got into me.

00:16:05.196 --> 00:16:07.766
I wonder if Woo Jae is eating well while he studies.

00:16:08.436 --> 00:16:09.736
He probably eats at the study cafe.

00:16:10.336 --> 00:16:13.776
But what happens now that Woo Jae failed his medical board exam again?

00:16:14.376 --> 00:16:17.046
Failing once can be a simple mistake or he was off by one row,

00:16:17.346 --> 00:16:20.816
but to fail both exams two years in a row is strange.

00:16:20.886 --> 00:16:21.886
Don't you think?

00:16:25.056 --> 00:16:26.256
There I go again. I must be crazy.

00:16:27.526 --> 00:16:29.126
Hey, why you...

00:16:34.566 --> 00:16:37.336
Happy birthday to you

00:16:37.696 --> 00:16:40.366
Happy birthday to you

00:16:40.806 --> 00:16:44.806
Happy birthday, dear Mom

00:16:45.376 --> 00:16:48.646
Happy birthday to you

00:16:50.576 --> 00:16:52.646
Where are you calling from?

00:16:53.046 --> 00:16:54.586
I just stepped out for a minute from studying.

00:16:54.886 --> 00:16:56.656
Make sure you take some breaks and get some fresh air, Mom.

00:16:57.586 --> 00:17:00.186
Thank you. You're the only one I can count on.

00:17:00.856 --> 00:17:03.496
Your dad just calls to ask for money.

00:17:06.366 --> 00:17:08.326
I'm sorry for letting you down this time.

00:17:08.826 --> 00:17:11.696
I was hoping to give you my license for your birthday.

00:17:13.266 --> 00:17:14.266
Woo Jae.

00:17:14.806 --> 00:17:16.376
Have you thought about a prep course?

00:17:17.606 --> 00:17:19.406
It's okay. The tuition is so expensive.

00:17:20.106 --> 00:17:22.606
I know what I did wrong. I'll study on my own.

00:17:23.676 --> 00:17:25.776
Okay.

00:17:35.626 --> 00:17:36.726
(Medicine, Gong Woo Jae)

00:17:36.796 --> 00:17:40.226
It appears to be an anxiety disorder from extreme stress over your exams.

00:17:40.566 --> 00:17:45.466
I'll prescribe an antidepressant. You should also attend therapy.

00:17:46.306 --> 00:17:48.166
(Hanguk University Hospital)

00:18:07.626 --> 00:18:10.596
- Delicious, right? It's to die for. - Yes.

00:18:12.126 --> 00:18:13.396
But, honey.

00:18:13.926 --> 00:18:17.336
Can't you move to another clinic that pays properly?

00:18:17.896 --> 00:18:21.236
No, how could I do that? Our clinic needs a PT, too.

00:18:23.976 --> 00:18:28.606
But honey, what if your uncle is hard on me at the service?

00:18:29.446 --> 00:18:30.846
Every time he sees me,

00:18:30.916 --> 00:18:34.216
he says we still don't have a child because I'm too old.

00:18:34.546 --> 00:18:36.046
- Then... - Yes?

00:18:36.556 --> 00:18:39.156
Why not stay late at the hair salon and take your time coming home?

00:18:39.826 --> 00:18:43.026
- Really? Can I really do that? - Of course.

00:18:46.026 --> 00:18:47.966
- Wait. Open wide. - What?

00:18:48.166 --> 00:18:50.136
- I'm stuffed. - Come on.

00:18:53.906 --> 00:18:56.206
- Then just take your time. - Okay.

00:18:58.106 --> 00:19:00.176
Thanks for switching spots with me.

00:19:02.576 --> 00:19:05.976
I've been here for 40 years. It's not like I'm going to run off.

00:19:06.886 --> 00:19:10.516
Okay, got it. All right, bye.

00:19:11.616 --> 00:19:13.126
Did you switch your turn for the payout?

00:19:13.256 --> 00:19:14.286
Yes.

00:19:14.886 --> 00:19:17.496
I was in a bind, but they switched. What a relief.

00:19:17.826 --> 00:19:20.896
- Oh, did you talk to Mom? - Yes.

00:19:21.526 --> 00:19:24.666
Ju Ah must be swamped with that home shopping show.

00:19:25.266 --> 00:19:28.906
I know. Of the two teams, only the top one will be kept.

00:19:29.806 --> 00:19:32.736
So the department's being cut in half.

00:19:32.836 --> 00:19:36.346
Yes. If she loses, her entire team gets fired,

00:19:36.776 --> 00:19:41.216
and she'll be demoted to staff. She's really worried.

00:19:41.716 --> 00:19:42.846
Yes, she must be.

00:19:43.556 --> 00:19:46.116
That's going to be really hard for her to take.

00:19:49.086 --> 00:19:52.526
What we at FG have been working on...

00:19:55.066 --> 00:20:01.006
our lovingly prepared Spring Summer collection.

00:20:02.566 --> 00:20:05.136
This season's concept is heritage...

00:20:05.936 --> 00:20:06.946
What?

00:20:08.646 --> 00:20:09.646
Hey!

00:20:10.776 --> 00:20:11.816
Eat up, then you can practice.

00:20:12.546 --> 00:20:14.146
Gosh, seriously.

00:20:18.286 --> 00:20:19.316
What?

00:20:19.886 --> 00:20:22.686
What's this? I'm cutting carbs for the show.

00:20:22.826 --> 00:20:27.466
Come on. You need carbs to be kind. Just eat it. It won't matter.

00:20:28.626 --> 00:20:32.636
Why so nice, Mr. Park Jun Hyeok? Did you forget we're rivals?

00:20:33.336 --> 00:20:37.776
Hey, wait. Don't tell me... You didn't poison the food, did you?

00:20:38.376 --> 00:20:39.846
Can't you see I'm eating it, too?

00:20:44.016 --> 00:20:47.316
I really wouldn't care if I got cut and you became the team lead.

00:20:47.386 --> 00:20:50.186
Hey. At least make it believable.

00:20:51.786 --> 00:20:52.816
Was it that obvious?

00:20:54.186 --> 00:20:57.556
No, seriously, go easy on me, okay? I'm the one who's desperate here.

00:20:57.796 --> 00:20:59.556
I mean, both of your parents are doctors.

00:20:59.556 --> 00:21:02.366
You have your medical license and were born with a silver spoon.

00:21:02.596 --> 00:21:05.836
Meanwhile, I don't have parents, and I have to scrape by on my own.

00:21:06.836 --> 00:21:09.036
You really have no clue, do you?

00:21:09.406 --> 00:21:13.606
If this were a misery contest, I'd give you a run for your money.

00:21:16.516 --> 00:21:17.516
Hey.

00:21:17.816 --> 00:21:19.716
Anyway, you seem pretty nervous.

00:21:20.046 --> 00:21:22.016
Your mom's a total natural on camera, though.

00:21:22.216 --> 00:21:25.256
Can we not talk about my family? I told you it was a secret.

00:21:26.256 --> 00:21:28.986
Honestly, though, I can see where your mom is coming from.

00:21:29.426 --> 00:21:33.166
If my kid got a medical license and then quit, I'd go crazy too.

00:21:34.366 --> 00:21:37.696
That's exactly when I stopped living as my mother's daughter.

00:21:38.336 --> 00:21:41.836
I want to live my life as me, Gong Ju Ah.

00:21:42.266 --> 00:21:46.746
Anyway, did you hear we're getting a new director after these layoffs?

00:21:46.876 --> 00:21:50.676
Yes, I heard that too. They say the new director is a foreigner.

00:21:50.946 --> 00:21:54.016
- From Argentina? - Yes. What was his name again?

00:21:54.446 --> 00:21:57.386
Iglesias, Facu, or Ignacio?

00:21:57.816 --> 00:22:00.686
Iglesias or whatever. I'll worry about that later.

00:22:01.726 --> 00:22:05.656
I just really want to get through this mess.

00:22:06.726 --> 00:22:11.636
The more I think about it, isn't this just too cruel?

00:22:11.766 --> 00:22:13.606
It's so cheap and low-down.

00:22:15.236 --> 00:22:18.406
Hey, what if we both just quit...

00:22:18.476 --> 00:22:21.376
and start our own brand together?

00:22:22.376 --> 00:22:25.416
It's because you're so impulsive and reckless...

00:22:25.476 --> 00:22:27.586
that your mom gives you such a hard time.

00:22:28.886 --> 00:22:30.116
Hey!

00:22:30.886 --> 00:22:33.326
Why are you always on my mom's side?

00:22:33.986 --> 00:22:35.086
That's ridiculous.

00:22:36.856 --> 00:22:38.026
Grandma.

00:22:38.626 --> 00:22:40.866
It's your mom's birthday. Did you call her?

00:22:41.526 --> 00:22:45.096
What's the big deal? It's not like she celebrates mine.

00:22:45.766 --> 00:22:46.766
Still.

00:22:47.266 --> 00:22:49.706
That's no way to treat the mother who gave birth to and raised you.

00:22:50.376 --> 00:22:53.476
Let's get that straight. She gave birth to me,

00:22:53.646 --> 00:22:55.506
but you're the one who raised me, Grandma.

00:22:56.716 --> 00:23:00.946
If you're late, don't bother coming here. Go to your mom's.

00:23:01.516 --> 00:23:03.286
- No way. - What?

00:23:03.856 --> 00:23:05.686
I'm serious. I'll lock you out and change the door code.

00:23:06.286 --> 00:23:08.556
Grandma! Come on.

00:23:11.926 --> 00:23:12.956
Unbelievable...

00:23:18.796 --> 00:23:20.336
Which one can I get for you?

00:23:20.806 --> 00:23:24.206
No idea. The person I'm buying for never likes anything I pick.

00:23:24.876 --> 00:23:29.146
- Just give me the most popular one. - And how many candles?

00:23:29.676 --> 00:23:31.646
One second. Let me see...

00:23:31.876 --> 00:23:35.886
How old is Dr. Han Seong Mi? Is she 52 or 53?

00:23:38.556 --> 00:23:41.856
Just give me 5 big ones and 5 small ones.

00:23:47.066 --> 00:23:50.036
What's with you? It's my birthday, and I don't even get a single call?

00:23:50.096 --> 00:23:52.596
I don't care how busy you are. You have no basic courtesy.

00:23:52.666 --> 00:23:54.266
How do you expect to get by in the real world?

00:23:54.766 --> 00:23:56.436
Come on.

00:23:56.936 --> 00:23:58.776
We just really don't get along.

00:23:59.336 --> 00:24:00.846
We're like oil and water.

00:24:12.356 --> 00:24:14.986
That brat. She left me on read again.

00:24:26.636 --> 00:24:27.706
Ju Ah? Is that you?

00:24:30.636 --> 00:24:31.636
Oh, thank you.

00:24:44.756 --> 00:24:46.956
To my eldest daughter, who's always working so hard.

00:24:47.426 --> 00:24:49.756
I'm sorry this is all I can do to celebrate with you.

00:24:50.496 --> 00:24:54.726
Happy birthday. Thank you for being my daughter.

00:24:58.896 --> 00:25:00.066
Mother.

00:25:00.866 --> 00:25:04.076
It's just a birthday. You shouldn't have bothered.

00:25:05.106 --> 00:25:06.476
I'm sorry.

00:25:06.976 --> 00:25:09.916
What are you sorry for? You're always saying that.

00:25:10.446 --> 00:25:12.246
I heard Jeong Han called you.

00:25:13.286 --> 00:25:15.546
Don't worry about the money. I've taken care of it.

00:25:15.846 --> 00:25:18.116
Did you ask the landlord for the deposit back?

00:25:18.116 --> 00:25:20.156
Or did you dip into your savings?

00:25:21.186 --> 00:25:22.756
I handled it.

00:25:23.456 --> 00:25:26.496
Come by this weekend if you're free. Don't rush if you're busy.

00:25:27.026 --> 00:25:31.936
- But I miss you so much. Just come. - Okay, I'll be there.

00:25:32.836 --> 00:25:34.636
Are you feeling okay?

00:25:35.006 --> 00:25:38.506
Of course. Now, eat up before it gets cold.

00:25:39.006 --> 00:25:41.776
If you feel lonely, just think of me.

00:25:42.106 --> 00:25:46.916
- I'm the expert on being lonely. - Okay.

00:25:47.686 --> 00:25:49.146
Thank you for the food, Mother.

00:26:00.526 --> 00:26:02.096
Oh, dear.

00:26:02.526 --> 00:26:05.936
I told you to sleep at your mom's. Why did you insist on coming here?

00:26:06.136 --> 00:26:08.566
I'm a grown woman. Why tell me to sleep at my mom's?

00:26:08.706 --> 00:26:11.706
I don't even remember sleeping in the same room as her as a kid.

00:26:11.806 --> 00:26:15.646
You should've given her the cake. Why buy it just to bring it here?

00:26:15.706 --> 00:26:19.846
I was going to! I was set to surprise her with it.

00:26:19.946 --> 00:26:24.216
But right when I was buying it, her text rubbed me the wrong way.

00:26:24.286 --> 00:26:26.086
- It just ruined the whole mood. - Honestly.

00:26:26.086 --> 00:26:29.356
Yes. Are you Mr. Go Il Sik's son?

00:26:29.956 --> 00:26:32.396
Yes, this is Gong Jeong Han.

00:26:32.656 --> 00:26:35.066
Yes, from Onjeong. That's right.

00:26:35.226 --> 00:26:37.666
And just like that, we're invisible again.

00:26:37.836 --> 00:26:40.506
He's always so nice to strangers.

00:26:40.936 --> 00:26:45.136
It's because of Grandfather. If Grandfather's sick,

00:26:45.206 --> 00:26:48.876
he hopes someone will help him out. So he always pays it forward.

00:26:49.076 --> 00:26:52.616
You mean the grandfather who ran off 30 years ago with another woman?

00:26:52.676 --> 00:26:55.946
- Dad's devotion is so touching. - Ju Ah!

00:26:55.946 --> 00:26:57.056
What?

00:26:57.216 --> 00:27:01.786
She's not wrong. Eat up and get to bed early, okay?

00:27:01.856 --> 00:27:03.656
- Okay. - Good night, Grandma.

00:27:03.656 --> 00:27:04.726
You too.

00:27:09.296 --> 00:27:12.796
You must be so stress-free, always saying what's on your mind.

00:27:12.936 --> 00:27:16.606
And you must never get angry, being so understanding all the time.

00:27:20.706 --> 00:27:22.506
(January 30, 2026)

00:27:22.506 --> 00:27:23.646
My dear husband.

00:27:24.216 --> 00:27:26.146
It's been a while since I've picked up a pen to write you.

00:27:27.416 --> 00:27:31.216
It's our eldest daughter-in-law's 53rd birthday.

00:27:32.286 --> 00:27:35.326
It seems like only yesterday she married into our family at 20.

00:27:35.486 --> 00:27:37.356
Look how much time has passed.

00:27:38.726 --> 00:27:41.966
Jeong Han was struggling to keep his clinic afloat,

00:27:42.126 --> 00:27:44.296
so I cashed out my savings pool to help him.

00:27:44.996 --> 00:27:46.336
The seventh anniversary...

00:27:46.336 --> 00:27:49.836
of your father's passing is this weekend.

00:28:01.186 --> 00:28:03.456
- Hello there. - Hello.

00:28:34.416 --> 00:28:35.616
Gi Cheol?

00:28:38.756 --> 00:28:39.916
Gi Cheol!

00:28:44.796 --> 00:28:47.066
You're my sons' father! Hey, Gong Gi Cheol!

00:28:47.926 --> 00:28:49.366
Hey, Gong Gi Cheol!

00:28:53.466 --> 00:28:56.836
Why pretend you don't know me? How can you just ignore me?

00:28:57.376 --> 00:29:01.206
How could you do this? How could you leave it all to me?

00:29:01.506 --> 00:29:06.176
You were alive all this time. You should've called the kids.

00:29:07.016 --> 00:29:10.116
Who are you? Hey, what are you doing to my husband?

00:29:10.356 --> 00:29:13.186
What did you just say? Is he Gong Gi... Gong Gi Cheol?

00:29:13.626 --> 00:29:15.056
Let go of me.

00:29:17.796 --> 00:29:22.196
- Who on earth is Gong Gi Cheol? - It's not you? It's really not you?

00:29:22.326 --> 00:29:24.536
I told you, he's not! You crazy old lady!

00:29:25.896 --> 00:29:27.466
I'm so sorry.

00:29:27.536 --> 00:29:30.536
Is "sorry" meant to fix everything? You won't get away with this!

00:29:30.606 --> 00:29:31.976
We're going to the police station, right now!

00:29:31.976 --> 00:29:34.546
Come on. Unbelievable. This is ridiculous.

00:29:34.906 --> 00:29:36.246
(Onjeong Police Substation)

00:29:36.246 --> 00:29:38.846
She said it was a mistake, ma'am.

00:29:38.976 --> 00:29:41.416
Please, for my sake, just let it go.

00:29:41.786 --> 00:29:44.486
But how can someone not recognize their own husband?

00:29:44.556 --> 00:29:47.986
You see, her husband...

00:29:48.226 --> 00:29:51.156
left home 30 years ago, so she can't recognize his face...

00:29:52.526 --> 00:29:56.466
Now, I see why he left. What a crazy old bat.

00:29:56.526 --> 00:29:58.336
No, she's not a crazy person.

00:29:58.396 --> 00:30:03.166
- She's Onjeong Market's pharmacist. - Look.

00:30:04.406 --> 00:30:06.206
Please come to my pharmacy.

00:30:06.276 --> 00:30:09.506
I'll treat your scrapes and give you some medicine.

00:30:09.876 --> 00:30:12.176
Forget it. This is just unbelievable.

00:30:12.376 --> 00:30:13.986
Just my luck!

00:30:14.486 --> 00:30:15.586
Honey, let's go.

00:30:16.386 --> 00:30:19.616
- Yes, thank you so much. - All right, take care.

00:30:22.256 --> 00:30:24.156
- Grandma! - Mom.

00:30:24.656 --> 00:30:29.026
Why did you all have to come? Chief, I'm sorry.

00:30:29.096 --> 00:30:30.096
It's no trouble at all.

00:30:30.166 --> 00:30:33.706
I'll make sure this never happens again.

00:30:34.966 --> 00:30:37.536
Mom, did you mistake someone for Dad again?

00:30:39.536 --> 00:30:40.576
This time,

00:30:41.306 --> 00:30:43.206
I was so sure it was your father.

00:30:43.916 --> 00:30:47.016
Everything's been smoothed over. You should take her home now.

00:30:49.616 --> 00:30:51.356
Okay, head on home.

00:30:56.226 --> 00:30:59.356
My goodness, Mom. You've really taken it up a notch.

00:30:59.526 --> 00:31:01.526
I know your grudge against Dad, but why did you hit the guy?

00:31:01.526 --> 00:31:02.866
And you choked him, too? Why?

00:31:03.796 --> 00:31:05.396
Just be quiet, and let's go.

00:31:06.566 --> 00:31:09.166
Grandma, from now on, let's go on your walks together.

00:31:09.766 --> 00:31:10.976
Forget it.

00:31:15.246 --> 00:31:16.606
(Police)

00:31:19.916 --> 00:31:21.946
- Chief? - Yes?

00:31:22.016 --> 00:31:25.186
What about him leaving 30 years ago? He just ran away?

00:31:25.256 --> 00:31:28.456
No, wait. After that long, wouldn't he be a missing person?

00:31:28.756 --> 00:31:31.756
You're new here, so you wouldn't know the story.

00:31:32.296 --> 00:31:33.296
What's the story?

00:31:33.826 --> 00:31:36.196
- It's complicated. - Come on. What is it?

00:31:36.726 --> 00:31:38.596
I get it. They must've had a bad fight.

00:31:38.666 --> 00:31:41.636
Now that you're in Onjeong, you'll find out soon enough.

00:31:42.036 --> 00:31:43.236
Just go on patrol.

00:31:43.536 --> 00:31:44.876
Yes, sir.

00:31:47.076 --> 00:31:48.606
Man, what was that about?

00:31:48.676 --> 00:31:50.206
(Onjeong Market)

00:31:50.276 --> 00:31:52.016
(Onjeong Market Merchants' Association)

00:31:59.116 --> 00:32:01.886
Like I said, give her a refund.

00:32:01.956 --> 00:32:04.156
- I already told you I can't. - Good grief.

00:32:04.296 --> 00:32:07.596
And why not? This is completely ridiculous!

00:32:07.896 --> 00:32:08.966
Give me a break.

00:32:09.496 --> 00:32:12.636
Director Yang Dong Ik of the Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic.

00:32:13.036 --> 00:32:14.636
Give her the refund, please.

00:32:14.636 --> 00:32:17.036
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic's Director Gong Jeong Han.

00:32:17.576 --> 00:32:19.776
That's not very fair of you. No refund.

00:32:19.836 --> 00:32:23.006
For goodness' sake. I keep saying I'm fine.

00:32:23.076 --> 00:32:27.316
See? She says she's fine. Why butt in and demand a refund?

00:32:27.686 --> 00:32:31.086
Practice with a conscience for once, will you?

00:32:31.486 --> 00:32:32.716
This old woman collects cardboard to get by.

00:32:33.016 --> 00:32:35.186
You charged her 380 dollars for medicine?

00:32:35.186 --> 00:32:36.586
That's just unconscionable.

00:32:36.656 --> 00:32:39.326
She came in sick, I examined her, and I wrote a prescription.

00:32:39.596 --> 00:32:41.596
The patient agreed to it, so what's the problem?

00:32:41.666 --> 00:32:45.266
- Goodness, I did agree to it. - But...

00:32:45.336 --> 00:32:49.606
- Please, don't fight. - She said you hid the details.

00:32:50.306 --> 00:32:54.006
That's because she has poor eyesight from diabetes, so it was pointless.

00:32:54.106 --> 00:32:55.876
You still should've asked.

00:32:56.176 --> 00:32:57.346
Why don't you stay out of this?

00:32:57.546 --> 00:33:02.286
- "You?" What's with the attitude? - What? Attitude?

00:33:02.816 --> 00:33:06.486
- Hey, Gong Dae Han! - "Hey?" Did you just call me "hey?"

00:33:06.556 --> 00:33:07.726
- Anyway... - Yes, I said "hey."

00:33:07.786 --> 00:33:09.426
- "Hey?" Really? - You call this practicing medicine?

00:33:09.486 --> 00:33:11.426
- Hey! You get over here! - What's your problem?

00:33:11.496 --> 00:33:15.966
- Get lost. - How many others did you rip off?

00:33:16.026 --> 00:33:18.436
- You're a total crook. - Hey! How dare you...

00:33:18.496 --> 00:33:21.006
- What are you, a thug? - What? Have you lost your mind?

00:33:21.066 --> 00:33:25.176
- Are you a gangster making threats? - Whatever.

00:33:25.806 --> 00:33:27.676
How much money do you think you can make like this?

00:33:27.746 --> 00:33:30.576
- What are you, a thug? - What? Have you lost your mind?

00:33:30.576 --> 00:33:31.816
- Are you a gangster making threats? - Whatever.

00:33:31.816 --> 00:33:33.916
- I can't with this guy. - Just go.

00:33:33.916 --> 00:33:35.286
What's all this commotion about?

00:33:35.886 --> 00:33:38.286
- Get lost! - What? Wait a minute.

00:33:38.716 --> 00:33:42.856
- Weren't they at the substation? - Hey!

00:33:43.256 --> 00:33:44.456
You don't need to break it up.

00:33:44.996 --> 00:33:45.996
What?

00:33:46.496 --> 00:33:48.596
You must be the new officer, so you probably don't know.

00:33:48.996 --> 00:33:52.936
Those two families always fight. It's childish, so leave them be.

00:33:52.996 --> 00:33:54.536
But why?

00:33:54.866 --> 00:33:57.436
That's it. I've had enough! Give her the refund now!

00:33:57.506 --> 00:34:01.606
- You're shameless! This medicine... - What? Seriously?

00:34:04.746 --> 00:34:08.346
- I said give her a refund, now! - I said no! I won't say it again.

00:34:09.486 --> 00:34:13.456
That's enough! I've had it! I'm leaving! Just let me go!

00:34:13.516 --> 00:34:16.226
No, ma'am, wait! Get your refund first, Ms. Park!

00:34:18.756 --> 00:34:21.666
- What? - You darn punk.

00:34:22.166 --> 00:34:25.766
- Did you just call me a punk? - Yes, I did. So what?

00:34:25.896 --> 00:34:28.266
Did you just call him a punk? Don't cross the line.

00:34:28.336 --> 00:34:30.066
You're the ones who crossed the line first.

00:34:30.066 --> 00:34:31.776
- Why is everyone acting like this? - Hey!

00:34:32.476 --> 00:34:35.646
You take the hard-earned money from people on public assistance...

00:34:35.706 --> 00:34:39.176
just to remodel your clinic, you money-grubbing snob.

00:34:39.246 --> 00:34:42.586
Playing the righteous doctor while your clinic is going under?

00:34:42.646 --> 00:34:45.316
You still act all high and mighty! You hypocrite!

00:34:46.116 --> 00:34:50.226
You're just a flashy, noisy Bucket.

00:34:50.496 --> 00:34:53.926
Hey! I told you not to call me "Bucket," didn't I?

00:34:54.396 --> 00:34:56.526
My name is Yang Dong Ik!

00:34:56.596 --> 00:34:59.866
Bucket. Clang, clang, clang. Bucket!

00:34:59.866 --> 00:35:01.666
- Will you shut your mouth? - Bucket.

00:35:01.736 --> 00:35:05.276
- I said, my name is Yang Dong Ik! - Clang, clang, Bucket.

00:35:05.276 --> 00:35:07.136
- Bucket. Oh, no! - My gosh.

00:35:07.136 --> 00:35:09.706
- Dad! - Dad, my clothes got all wet.

00:35:09.776 --> 00:35:10.776
Stop it!

00:35:12.316 --> 00:35:14.746
Man, my pants are soaked. Good grief.

00:35:18.056 --> 00:35:20.216
- That son of a... - Bye, Bucket.

00:35:31.966 --> 00:35:33.066
So that's what this is.

00:35:33.536 --> 00:35:36.666
The wife of the grandfather from this clinic...

00:35:37.136 --> 00:35:40.606
and the husband of the grandmother who's the hospital's pharmacist...

00:35:40.906 --> 00:35:43.246
They fell for each other and ran off in the middle of the night.

00:35:43.546 --> 00:35:44.546
Thirty years ago.

00:35:44.916 --> 00:35:49.246
So that's why their kids are always at each other's throats.

00:35:49.416 --> 00:35:53.186
There's a lot more to it than that. You'll find out in due time.

00:35:53.886 --> 00:35:56.426
They're famous in this market for being sworn enemies.

00:35:56.756 --> 00:35:57.896
I see.

00:35:58.596 --> 00:36:00.566
Famous sworn enemies.

00:36:01.726 --> 00:36:03.766
- Can I take a look? - No, you can't.

00:36:05.066 --> 00:36:09.136
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:36:09.136 --> 00:36:10.936
(Pharmacy)

00:36:18.376 --> 00:36:22.086
Why is he always so extra? Who does he think he is, so nosy?

00:36:22.346 --> 00:36:24.586
Is he taking herbal medicine behind my back or something?

00:36:24.856 --> 00:36:26.486
Has he been drinking human blood like a vampire?

00:36:27.216 --> 00:36:28.786
He never ages, and he's so full of energy.

00:36:30.126 --> 00:36:32.956
I know. I keep saying we should move the clinic to the apartment complex.

00:36:33.256 --> 00:36:36.326
Why did we waste all this money on remodeling?

00:36:36.496 --> 00:36:39.266
As if a high-end clinic like this can survive in a traditional market.

00:36:39.336 --> 00:36:41.436
You know Dad is dead set against moving.

00:36:46.806 --> 00:36:49.876
Your wife went to the clinic heads' wives' meeting, didn't she?

00:36:50.106 --> 00:36:52.516
I know. I'm just making sure that's really where she went.

00:36:52.976 --> 00:36:55.786
She's been with us for over 15 years. You still suspect her?

00:36:56.386 --> 00:37:00.856
Afraid she'll leave with someone, like our mom or Eun Bin's mom did?

00:37:03.326 --> 00:37:06.356
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

00:37:12.666 --> 00:37:15.336
- Where are you? Send a proof shot. - This is delicious.

00:37:15.406 --> 00:37:18.136
- It's delicious and so clean. - Really?

00:37:18.206 --> 00:37:21.306
- I'll bring the kids next time. - You should.

00:37:24.076 --> 00:37:25.546
- It tastes so simple and clean. - Isn't it so good?

00:37:26.846 --> 00:37:27.846
This is so good.

00:37:30.686 --> 00:37:34.256
My husband recently got an offer to franchise his clinic,

00:37:34.586 --> 00:37:38.996
- and I'm not sure what to do. - What's to think about? Look at us.

00:37:39.096 --> 00:37:41.266
The moment we changed our sign, our bookings doubled.

00:37:41.666 --> 00:37:43.696
You can't underestimate brand recognition.

00:37:45.096 --> 00:37:46.396
What about you guys? Not interested?

00:37:47.096 --> 00:37:50.876
It must be tough with the regulars out in the sticks.

00:37:51.336 --> 00:37:52.906
It's not tough at all.

00:37:53.636 --> 00:37:56.076
We actually just expanded.

00:37:58.146 --> 00:38:01.946
We're having a grand reopening. Please come by if you have time.

00:38:08.026 --> 00:38:09.626
Oh, so this is why you wanted to get together.

00:38:11.426 --> 00:38:13.326
By the way, did you get something done to your face?

00:38:16.926 --> 00:38:19.266
You know I was blessed with natural beauty.

00:38:19.866 --> 00:38:24.306
I guess you forgot I was crowned Miss Dolsan Gat Kimchi.

00:38:25.106 --> 00:38:26.406
That's right. You were.

00:38:26.706 --> 00:38:30.376
And you met Director Yang when he judged the pageant, right?

00:38:30.916 --> 00:38:33.616
Yes. Oh, my dear husband.

00:38:33.916 --> 00:38:36.616
I'm the one who made the first move and snagged him, you know.

00:38:38.986 --> 00:38:40.556
But every time I see you,

00:38:40.756 --> 00:38:44.296
you're decked out from head to toe in designer brands.

00:38:45.426 --> 00:38:47.326
With the money my husband works himself to the bone for,

00:38:47.766 --> 00:38:49.526
I feel bad about buying even a pair of socks.

00:38:51.436 --> 00:38:55.606
Me, buy this? My husband buys it all for me.

00:38:57.106 --> 00:39:01.176
I guess that's the perk of being the second wife to a rich man.

00:39:01.246 --> 00:39:02.246
You've got to enjoy it...

00:39:03.246 --> 00:39:04.676
Oh, sorry.

00:39:05.246 --> 00:39:07.046
That just came out with no filter.

00:39:10.286 --> 00:39:11.356
It's because you're old.

00:39:11.856 --> 00:39:15.856
They say when you get old, you just say whatever comes to mind.

00:39:19.356 --> 00:39:20.356
Please, eat.

00:39:25.096 --> 00:39:27.806
Yes, hello. Did you check the photo I sent?

00:39:28.736 --> 00:39:31.506
Look, I specifically requested a brand-new item.

00:39:31.706 --> 00:39:35.846
It's unacceptable for the bag to be scratched up like this.

00:39:36.476 --> 00:39:39.446
I was too busy to return it, so I just used it this time.

00:39:39.916 --> 00:39:42.846
But if this happens next time, I'm taking my business elsewhere.

00:39:46.516 --> 00:39:47.526
What?

00:39:48.056 --> 00:39:49.386
Eun Bin, what are you doing?

00:39:49.926 --> 00:39:52.326
Can't you tell? I'm packing a lunchbox.

00:39:52.696 --> 00:39:54.696
I know, but why are you the one packing it?

00:39:55.226 --> 00:39:56.526
I'm taking it to someone.

00:39:56.826 --> 00:39:57.836
Who?

00:39:58.136 --> 00:40:02.106
It's not like you'd know them. Why do you keep asking? So annoying.

00:40:02.166 --> 00:40:03.306
Seriously...

00:40:04.006 --> 00:40:06.976
- Hey! Where are the beef patties? - The patties? You ate them.

00:40:07.036 --> 00:40:08.246
What, they're all gone?

00:40:08.606 --> 00:40:12.016
- Why? - Don't ask why. Just make more.

00:40:12.116 --> 00:40:13.876
Make what? You want me to make beef patties now?

00:40:14.146 --> 00:40:16.946
Why are you making me repeat myself?

00:40:18.216 --> 00:40:23.056
- Fine, I'll make them. Just wait. - Seriously. Make three.

00:40:23.686 --> 00:40:26.926
Gosh, that's a lot. You'll get fat. What if you get a double chin?

00:40:26.996 --> 00:40:30.426
I told you! They're not for me! Gosh, seriously.

00:40:30.496 --> 00:40:33.036
Okay, fine. I'll make them. Just wait.

00:40:33.396 --> 00:40:36.336
Why can't you just do what I ask? You talk so much. It's so annoying.

00:40:36.436 --> 00:40:38.376
- All right. - Stop touching my face!

00:40:38.776 --> 00:40:39.776
Seriously...

00:40:43.206 --> 00:40:44.216
Unbelievable.

00:40:51.916 --> 00:40:52.916
Woo Jae!

00:40:54.356 --> 00:40:55.426
What is it now?

00:40:58.156 --> 00:40:59.256
Ta-da!

00:41:01.366 --> 00:41:05.336
- What are you doing? - You're studying for your boards,

00:41:05.396 --> 00:41:08.166
so I'm playing the devoted girlfriend.

00:41:08.636 --> 00:41:10.266
But I'm not your boyfriend.

00:41:10.336 --> 00:41:13.376
Try these short rib patties. They're amazing.

00:41:13.436 --> 00:41:16.006
If our grandparents and parents found out about this,

00:41:16.076 --> 00:41:18.146
they'd all have a heart attack.

00:41:18.216 --> 00:41:19.276
Exactly.

00:41:19.646 --> 00:41:23.446
Doesn't that make our story tragic? We're just like Romeo and Juliet.

00:41:23.516 --> 00:41:26.116
That only works if Romeo actually loves Juliet.

00:41:27.116 --> 00:41:30.686
Eun Bin, I've told you. I only see you as a little sister.

00:41:30.756 --> 00:41:35.366
Come on, you're just pushing me away because you can't date right now.

00:41:35.466 --> 00:41:39.036
Besides, our families' feud is our parents' business.

00:41:39.096 --> 00:41:42.736
If your grandfather catches you, he'll rip all your hair out.

00:41:45.076 --> 00:41:46.076
He wouldn't.

00:41:52.416 --> 00:41:54.616
Father, shouldn't you have some lunch?

00:41:54.946 --> 00:41:56.016
Forget it!

00:41:56.516 --> 00:41:59.916
Even if you have no appetite, have a bite so you don't waste away.

00:42:00.286 --> 00:42:04.826
If I waste away, I'll die. So what? Why live any longer at my age?

00:42:05.296 --> 00:42:08.666
Please don't say that. Come on out when you get hungry, okay?

00:42:08.726 --> 00:42:10.426
No, I said I don't want any!

00:42:33.816 --> 00:42:36.626
Dad has a closet full of snacks. You know that.

00:42:37.226 --> 00:42:40.326
I know, but he only eats junk food.

00:42:40.556 --> 00:42:43.626
I swapped them for healthy ones, and he yelled at me so much.

00:42:43.996 --> 00:42:46.336
He threw a huge fit, and then went to the market...

00:42:46.396 --> 00:42:47.966
and restocked it with all sorts of junk again.

00:42:52.006 --> 00:42:53.006
Aren't you going to eat?

00:42:54.006 --> 00:42:55.576
I already had brunch, remember?

00:42:56.076 --> 00:42:57.206
Right.

00:42:57.816 --> 00:43:02.216
So that's why there's no good food. You already had something nice.

00:43:02.516 --> 00:43:03.586
What? There's no good food?

00:43:03.946 --> 00:43:05.386
You've practically licked the plates clean.

00:43:06.186 --> 00:43:09.286
And I thought you were always on a diet.

00:43:09.356 --> 00:43:10.956
You call what you just ate a diet?

00:43:10.956 --> 00:43:12.356
You love salt, and you eat too much and too late.

00:43:12.856 --> 00:43:15.626
You'll never lose the weight if you keep eating like that.

00:43:16.626 --> 00:43:20.736
Can we eat out for lunch sometimes? Must you always come home to eat?

00:43:21.466 --> 00:43:22.536
Why? The clinic is just around the corner.

00:43:22.636 --> 00:43:24.406
Please. You just come home to check on her.

00:43:24.806 --> 00:43:25.836
What? I'm not checking up on her.

00:43:26.206 --> 00:43:29.576
All couples do this. Didn't you know they all use tracking apps now?

00:43:30.006 --> 00:43:32.746
What are you talking about? Go ask any couple on the street.

00:43:32.816 --> 00:43:33.816
Nobody does that.

00:43:34.546 --> 00:43:39.486
Who cares what other people do? As long as it works for us.

00:43:40.586 --> 00:43:43.686
Right. What a perfect couple. Live happily ever after.

00:43:44.356 --> 00:43:46.326
Hey, don't be like that. You should do it, too.

00:43:46.796 --> 00:43:48.826
You should install a tracking app on your husband's phone.

00:43:49.126 --> 00:43:52.366
He might lie about going to work and go to an arcade, you never know.

00:43:53.736 --> 00:43:57.636
Tell him to stop messing around with stocks or pyramid schemes.

00:43:58.106 --> 00:44:00.076
I'm kicking you both out of this house.

00:44:00.776 --> 00:44:04.146
He's not like that anymore. He's been working so hard lately.

00:44:04.846 --> 00:44:07.616
Fine. Save your money and move out while you're still mooching off us.

00:44:07.816 --> 00:44:09.046
What do you mean, "mooching?"

00:44:09.386 --> 00:44:11.716
As long as our father is alive, this is my home too.

00:44:12.056 --> 00:44:14.626
If you're going to stay, at least wash your own dishes.

00:44:14.986 --> 00:44:15.986
You have no shame.

00:44:16.086 --> 00:44:19.426
I help out at the clinic, but your wife does nothing.

00:44:19.556 --> 00:44:21.766
My wife doesn't just sit at home. She does a lot around here.

00:44:22.196 --> 00:44:24.896
And it's not like I'm making you work for free. I pay you a salary.

00:44:25.266 --> 00:44:26.896
And you don't contribute a dime to the household expenses.

00:44:27.196 --> 00:44:28.806
How many years have you been this shameless?

00:44:29.836 --> 00:44:34.376
Come on, honey, stop. It's only until Hyun Bin comes back.

00:44:34.446 --> 00:44:36.446
They could use Hyun Bin's room until he gets back.

00:44:37.646 --> 00:44:38.816
Hyun Bin is moving back?

00:44:39.576 --> 00:44:41.916
Did you hear from Hyun Bin?

00:44:43.216 --> 00:44:44.216
No.

00:44:45.516 --> 00:44:48.056
That kid... He's the eldest son,

00:44:48.526 --> 00:44:49.526
and he's past the age to get married.

00:44:50.356 --> 00:44:51.526
How long will he keep wandering around?

00:45:04.576 --> 00:45:08.376
(International Airport Information, Duty Free, Customs)

00:45:36.936 --> 00:45:38.306
Hello, nice to meet you.

00:45:38.306 --> 00:45:39.306
Hi.

00:45:39.306 --> 00:45:42.276
- Great day to arrive in Korea. - Yes.

00:45:42.906 --> 00:45:43.906
Yes.

00:45:50.946 --> 00:45:51.956
Please take me to this address.

00:45:52.316 --> 00:45:55.726
It's 298-2 Sunbok-ri, Gopyeong-eup, Ganghwa-gun.

00:45:57.086 --> 00:45:58.096
Okay.

00:46:08.306 --> 00:46:09.836
Smells like Korea.

00:46:15.646 --> 00:46:19.116
I've really missed this murky, smoggy air.

00:46:19.846 --> 00:46:22.286
Looks like you were away on a long trip.

00:46:23.046 --> 00:46:25.156
Not a trip. I was studying abroad.

00:46:25.756 --> 00:46:28.126
You know Argentina? The soccer powerhouse.

00:46:28.556 --> 00:46:29.556
Right, yes.

00:46:30.486 --> 00:46:32.656
I lived in a city called Palermo.

00:46:32.996 --> 00:46:35.966
It's kind of like the Beverly Hills of Buenos Aires.

00:46:36.626 --> 00:46:40.236
It's a vibrant hub of fashion, art, and fine dining.

00:46:40.396 --> 00:46:41.406
I see.

00:46:42.806 --> 00:46:44.836
I'm just back in Korea for a little while.

00:46:45.276 --> 00:46:47.636
Just for about a year. Short but intense.

00:46:48.376 --> 00:46:50.706
Because someone is desperately looking for me.

00:46:52.346 --> 00:46:53.576
Guess who?

00:46:55.616 --> 00:46:56.746
Who could it be?

00:46:57.546 --> 00:46:59.056
I'm not telling.

00:47:02.286 --> 00:47:04.126
One second.

00:47:04.796 --> 00:47:05.796
What?

00:47:06.456 --> 00:47:08.296
- Hello? - Pacu Nacho!

00:47:08.496 --> 00:47:09.496
Vice President.

00:47:09.926 --> 00:47:10.926
You made it?

00:47:11.536 --> 00:47:13.836
I'll text you the hotel address. Get some rest.

00:47:14.236 --> 00:47:16.636
I'll head over after work. Meet me in the lobby tonight.

00:47:16.906 --> 00:47:18.206
I have somewhere to be first.

00:47:18.436 --> 00:47:19.906
I'll contact you when I'm back, okay?

00:47:27.276 --> 00:47:29.046
(Hwangbo Hye Su, Vice President, Strategic Planning Division)

00:47:31.256 --> 00:47:34.486
(Taehan Group)

00:47:36.826 --> 00:47:39.596
- Who's up first today? - Team Manager Gong Ju Ah.

00:47:40.256 --> 00:47:42.466
Oh, the one from medical school?

00:48:06.016 --> 00:48:09.956
Let's get a full shot of the outfit, not just the coat.

00:48:10.026 --> 00:48:12.326
Yes, got it. I'm getting nervous, too.

00:48:15.096 --> 00:48:17.226
Ms. Gong, the VP is here.

00:48:31.646 --> 00:48:35.546
All right, today's brand is FG from the Taehan Group!

00:48:35.716 --> 00:48:36.946
And for a special treat today...

00:48:37.016 --> 00:48:38.886
So, she has to be number one in sales today, or she's out, right?

00:48:39.356 --> 00:48:40.816
Yikes, that's so nerve-racking.

00:48:41.086 --> 00:48:42.086
Please welcome her.

00:48:43.226 --> 00:48:47.156
Yes, we at FG have poured our hearts into preparing this SS collection,

00:48:47.326 --> 00:48:49.826
and I'm so happy to be able to present it to you myself.

00:48:49.896 --> 00:48:52.466
Ju Ah is so photogenic. She looks gorgeous.

00:48:52.696 --> 00:48:53.696
You're gorgeous, too.

00:48:55.606 --> 00:49:00.236
This season's concept is "Heritage and Modernity."

00:49:01.176 --> 00:49:05.176
Then, why don't you tell us about the outfit you're wearing?

00:49:05.346 --> 00:49:06.346
Yes, of course.

00:49:06.746 --> 00:49:10.886
It's a sporty look, pairing a skirt with this very vibrant jacket.

00:49:10.946 --> 00:49:13.186
Wow, that's incredibly practical.

00:49:13.686 --> 00:49:16.826
Yes, the jacket is especially great because it has a zipper on the side,

00:49:16.886 --> 00:49:19.396
which makes it incredibly easy to put on and take off.

00:49:19.496 --> 00:49:22.596
Could you show us how it works?

00:49:22.696 --> 00:49:24.126
- Of course. - Great.

00:49:24.196 --> 00:49:25.296
So you just unzip it like...

00:49:31.776 --> 00:49:34.746
See? It's very simple. You just unzip it...

00:49:41.886 --> 00:49:42.886
What's wrong with her?

00:49:44.316 --> 00:49:46.556
- What's she doing? - Oh, no.

00:49:54.196 --> 00:49:55.966
Just take your time and pull it up.

00:50:04.236 --> 00:50:05.236
Oh, my!

00:50:05.776 --> 00:50:07.736
Oh, no! My goodness.

00:50:12.576 --> 00:50:15.716
Dr. Han! You must see this! It's a wardrobe malfunction.

00:50:15.786 --> 00:50:19.316
Her jacket ripped! They said she's the team lead. My gosh.

00:50:19.386 --> 00:50:22.686
- How humiliating. - Oh, no!

00:50:22.956 --> 00:50:26.326
- I can't watch. This is awful. - I feel so bad for her.

00:50:29.966 --> 00:50:32.466
(Today's Home Shopping Wardrobe Malfunction)

00:50:35.436 --> 00:50:38.776
Gosh, I'm so embarrassed I could die.

00:50:39.806 --> 00:50:42.806
Wow, how am I ever going to live this down?

00:50:50.316 --> 00:50:51.316
Ju Ah.

00:50:54.826 --> 00:50:55.886
Goodness.

00:50:59.426 --> 00:51:00.656
Hey, are you okay?

00:51:03.526 --> 00:51:05.836
Did yours go okay?

00:51:06.536 --> 00:51:07.696
You didn't mess up, did you?

00:51:09.566 --> 00:51:10.566
No.

00:51:11.166 --> 00:51:13.476
- I'm sorry. - What are you sorry for?

00:51:15.806 --> 00:51:19.816
What am I going to do? I think it's all over social media.

00:51:20.816 --> 00:51:25.556
How on earth did this even happen? I just don't get it.

00:51:26.316 --> 00:51:27.616
Try not to let it get to you.

00:51:57.646 --> 00:51:58.686
Oh, man.

00:51:59.386 --> 00:52:00.686
This is killing me.

00:52:02.726 --> 00:52:04.256
Where the heck is he?

00:52:14.496 --> 00:52:15.536
Sir!

00:52:27.246 --> 00:52:28.246
There he is.

00:52:36.886 --> 00:52:37.886
Sir!

00:52:38.556 --> 00:52:39.556
And who might you be?

00:52:39.956 --> 00:52:43.596
In Episode 531 of "I Am Wild,"

00:52:44.026 --> 00:52:48.236
you took some winter-dried greens, pork, baby potatoes, and carrots,

00:52:48.566 --> 00:52:50.436
threw them on a cast-iron lid, and boiled them...

00:52:50.906 --> 00:52:52.636
to create your famous radish green curry over rice.

00:52:53.006 --> 00:52:54.576
You're Mr. Bae Bong Nam, aren't you?

00:52:54.836 --> 00:52:55.946
Yes, I am, but...

00:52:56.676 --> 00:52:57.676
I can't believe it.

00:52:59.876 --> 00:53:01.046
It's such an honor to meet you, sir.

00:53:01.546 --> 00:53:02.546
Thank you.

00:53:06.316 --> 00:53:09.086
Thank you, Lord!

00:53:16.866 --> 00:53:18.696
Let me just put this over here.

00:53:19.266 --> 00:53:21.166
The apples go at the end...

00:53:21.936 --> 00:53:22.936
And over here...

00:53:25.736 --> 00:53:27.776
- Seon Hae. - Yes?

00:53:28.876 --> 00:53:32.576
Where are the daughters-in-law? Why are you doing all this alone?

00:53:33.076 --> 00:53:36.316
What do you mean alone, Uncle? I'm here. Woo Jae, too.

00:53:36.746 --> 00:53:38.046
Then where's your wife?

00:53:38.686 --> 00:53:40.756
This is just ridiculous.

00:53:41.256 --> 00:53:43.756
Hui Gyeong has work. You know she's at the salon.

00:53:44.086 --> 00:53:46.856
Mom will be here soon. She's busy with work, you know.

00:53:47.696 --> 00:53:48.696
And Jeong Han?

00:53:49.596 --> 00:53:52.136
Where is the eldest son? Why are you starting without him?

00:53:52.266 --> 00:53:55.436
Uncle, it's still early. Why are you getting so worked up?

00:53:55.536 --> 00:53:58.436
But dear, why isn't Hui Gyeong here yet?

00:53:58.506 --> 00:54:00.436
I actually told her to come a little later.

00:54:00.906 --> 00:54:02.276
I'll go get her now.

00:54:03.076 --> 00:54:04.776
I'll go get Dad.

00:54:12.056 --> 00:54:14.216
- I'll be right back. You go ahead. - Okay.

00:54:14.216 --> 00:54:15.426
- Dae Han. - Seong Mi.

00:54:16.256 --> 00:54:17.486
Go on inside.

00:54:17.656 --> 00:54:20.656
Uncle's been here for a while, making a scene, asking for everyone.

00:54:20.726 --> 00:54:21.726
- See you in a bit. - Okay.

00:54:22.196 --> 00:54:24.226
Mom, you didn't see Dad on your way here, did you?

00:54:24.326 --> 00:54:27.466
- Why? Isn't he home? - No. I'll go get him.

00:54:30.436 --> 00:54:31.736
Good grief.

00:54:48.786 --> 00:54:50.726
Dad!

00:54:52.226 --> 00:54:53.996
Where could he be? He's not even answering his phone.

00:54:55.466 --> 00:54:56.866
(Paramedics)

00:54:56.926 --> 00:54:59.236
BP's 80 over 50. His pulse is dropping.

00:55:00.036 --> 00:55:03.466
It's likely a myocardial infarction. I suspect it's the anterior wall.

00:55:03.666 --> 00:55:07.506
He needs a coronary angiography. Get him to a hospital right now.

00:55:07.606 --> 00:55:08.846
- Got it. - Right.

00:55:09.676 --> 00:55:13.276
Sir. I'm right here with you.

00:55:13.816 --> 00:55:16.546
We've contacted your children, so please don't worry.

00:55:16.616 --> 00:55:18.386
Just try and relax.

00:55:22.786 --> 00:55:24.186
The person you're trying to reach is unavailable...

00:55:25.856 --> 00:55:28.626
Why isn't he picking up? Where did he go now?

00:55:33.466 --> 00:55:35.366
(Neungi Mushroom Chicken Soup)

00:55:36.166 --> 00:55:41.106
(Dr. Han Seong Mi)

00:56:05.136 --> 00:56:06.366
(Isulro Soju)

00:56:08.706 --> 00:56:09.706
Excuse me.

00:56:14.536 --> 00:56:16.046
(Isulro Soju)

00:56:18.616 --> 00:56:21.276
Sir, can we get another bottle of soju over here?

00:56:23.446 --> 00:56:24.446
Excuse me?

00:56:24.846 --> 00:56:26.286
Soju.

00:56:31.586 --> 00:56:33.626
- Thanks. - Sure.

00:56:39.336 --> 00:56:40.336
What is it?

00:56:51.206 --> 00:56:52.946
You just look really familiar.

00:56:53.476 --> 00:56:55.886
I doubt that. This is my first time here.

00:56:55.946 --> 00:56:57.746
Yes, me too.

00:56:59.856 --> 00:57:01.286
You don't work here?

00:57:05.796 --> 00:57:07.326
I'm so sorry.

00:57:07.696 --> 00:57:08.866
No worries.

00:57:09.526 --> 00:57:10.526
But still...

00:57:11.366 --> 00:57:13.236
You just look so familiar.

00:57:15.706 --> 00:57:17.906
Did you see that home shopping thing?

00:57:18.206 --> 00:57:22.676
- What? - That viral wardrobe malfunction.

00:57:23.076 --> 00:57:24.606
Is that what you're thinking of?

00:57:25.516 --> 00:57:26.516
What?

00:57:31.146 --> 00:57:35.186
People are so mean. As if they never make mistakes.

00:57:35.786 --> 00:57:39.826
Something like that is a disaster, isn't it?

00:57:39.996 --> 00:57:41.596
When something like that happens to someone,

00:57:41.656 --> 00:57:45.766
can't people just look the other way?

00:57:45.836 --> 00:57:49.106
But no, they have to go and immortalize it online,

00:57:49.206 --> 00:57:51.236
and tear that person down just to get a kick out of it?

00:57:52.776 --> 00:57:56.446
Seriously, some people have zero compassion.

00:57:57.546 --> 00:57:59.276
The person it happened to...

00:58:00.146 --> 00:58:04.116
could be so humiliated they want to die, you know?

00:58:06.886 --> 00:58:09.026
- Right. - So...

00:58:09.826 --> 00:58:13.226
please just pretend you don't recognize me.

00:58:14.326 --> 00:58:16.566
You can do that much for me, can't you?

00:58:18.066 --> 00:58:19.066
Okay.

00:58:48.966 --> 00:58:50.966
(Habi Hair Salon)

00:58:52.566 --> 00:58:53.566
What?

00:58:57.066 --> 00:58:58.566
My honey's not at the shop.

00:59:16.926 --> 00:59:18.486
I'm thinking of growing it out.

00:59:18.926 --> 00:59:21.926
- You'd look pretty either way. - This is my hair without bangs.

00:59:38.576 --> 00:59:41.576
(Our Deepest Condolences)

00:59:57.926 --> 00:59:58.936
Wait.

00:59:59.696 --> 01:00:03.236
- Alone? Where's Hui Gyeong? - What?

01:00:04.206 --> 01:00:07.236
Well... What about Jeong Han? He's still not here?

01:00:07.306 --> 01:00:09.876
No. We can't reach him, and he's not at the clinic.

01:00:10.146 --> 01:00:12.816
Forget it. Let's just start without them.

01:00:53.956 --> 01:00:55.586
I'm heading out.

01:00:58.186 --> 01:01:01.656
Why are you leaving already? Please wait. I packed you some food.

01:01:01.726 --> 01:01:02.726
There's no need.

01:01:03.596 --> 01:01:04.596
Oh, Jeong Han.

01:01:06.866 --> 01:01:07.866
Honey.

01:01:08.136 --> 01:01:10.066
- I'm here. - Jeong Han.

01:01:10.336 --> 01:01:13.276
What took you so long? Why didn't you answer your phone?

01:01:14.176 --> 01:01:15.976
Well, it's just...

01:01:17.506 --> 01:01:18.546
Are you...

01:01:19.246 --> 01:01:21.276
Have you been drinking?

01:01:22.516 --> 01:01:24.346
Yes, I... I had a little to drink.

01:01:24.946 --> 01:01:26.256
Of all the nerve...

01:01:26.556 --> 01:01:29.256
Now, I've seen everything.

01:01:30.056 --> 01:01:33.526
Seon Hae! Is this how you raised your children?

01:01:33.796 --> 01:01:34.856
Uncle!

01:01:35.296 --> 01:01:37.526
Mom is too old for you to be lecturing her on parenting.

01:01:37.666 --> 01:01:38.666
Dae Han.

01:01:38.966 --> 01:01:40.466
This little brat...

01:01:40.736 --> 01:01:42.506
You're going to talk back to me, too?

01:01:42.836 --> 01:01:47.206
I'm glad I didn't bring my family. I didn't want them to see this mess.

01:01:48.006 --> 01:01:51.646
So what if one's a doctor and the other has a Ph.D.?

01:01:52.076 --> 01:01:55.886
This is what happens when kids grow up without a father.

01:01:55.916 --> 01:01:57.386
That's not it at all.

01:01:58.546 --> 01:02:01.956
- What do you mean? - He's the one who walked out on us!

01:02:02.016 --> 01:02:03.026
What did you say?

01:02:03.626 --> 01:02:05.996
What's gotten into everyone? Stop it, all of you.

01:02:06.156 --> 01:02:08.756
Ever since Dad left, Mom has been all alone.

01:02:09.296 --> 01:02:12.596
She cared for Grandfather until the end, provided for us,

01:02:12.666 --> 01:02:14.636
and has spent her life raising her own grandchildren.

01:02:15.066 --> 01:02:17.366
She endured all those years completely on her own.

01:02:17.666 --> 01:02:20.736
Dad's the one who had an affair and left home.

01:02:20.806 --> 01:02:24.706
- Why are you taking it out on Mom? - Had your mother been a good wife,

01:02:25.076 --> 01:02:27.246
my brother never would've left for another woman!

01:02:27.316 --> 01:02:31.116
Uncle! Mom, that's it. We're not doing this memorial.

01:02:31.416 --> 01:02:33.386
Why hold a memorial for Grandfather when his own son doesn't even care?

01:02:33.456 --> 01:02:37.926
Why should you be humiliated for it? And another thing.

01:02:38.426 --> 01:02:40.656
Let's just consider our father dead. Darn it.

01:02:41.656 --> 01:02:45.736
Fine. Good idea, you brat.

01:02:46.196 --> 01:02:49.466
You're right. He'd be better off dead somewhere.

01:02:49.766 --> 01:02:53.776
If I were him, I wouldn't visit this madhouse!

01:02:54.036 --> 01:02:56.506
Gosh, I can't even with this...

01:03:19.666 --> 01:03:21.536
Honey, I was waiting outside.

01:03:21.596 --> 01:03:24.866
I came in since your uncle left. Smart, right?

01:03:26.206 --> 01:03:29.976
Hey. Did your uncle make you angry, sweetie?

01:03:37.086 --> 01:03:40.416
Where on earth were you drinking to show up and act like this?

01:03:40.986 --> 01:03:43.786
I booked an appointment for Mr. Go at a big hospital.

01:03:44.156 --> 01:03:47.926
But he missed his appointment and wasn't answering his phone.

01:03:48.126 --> 01:03:51.696
What are you even talking about? Is this about a patient again?

01:03:51.896 --> 01:03:54.366
So I rushed over to his house to check on him.

01:03:54.436 --> 01:03:57.366
And what? Did he drop dead or something?

01:03:57.736 --> 01:04:00.406
You... How can you be so...

01:04:00.476 --> 01:04:03.976
What? What did I do? Are you blaming me for this, too?

01:04:04.406 --> 01:04:06.376
Gosh, forget it.

01:04:07.316 --> 01:04:09.016
How could you?

01:04:09.286 --> 01:04:12.756
How can you just ignore your family and do whatever you want?

01:04:12.956 --> 01:04:15.826
You dump everything on my mom and live however you want, too!

01:04:16.556 --> 01:04:17.556
What?

01:04:20.156 --> 01:04:22.396
I'm so sick of you.

01:04:23.226 --> 01:04:25.496
Do you even know what my life is like out there?

01:04:26.066 --> 01:04:28.666
Do you have any idea what my life is like?

01:04:30.136 --> 01:04:31.266
I regret this so much.

01:04:31.966 --> 01:04:35.036
I truly regret marrying you.

01:04:35.406 --> 01:04:39.216
Honestly, if it weren't for Ju Ah, I never would have married you.

01:04:40.616 --> 01:04:43.186
Hey, the feeling is mutual. Darn it...

01:04:48.856 --> 01:04:50.826
Whenever my mom and dad fight,

01:04:51.086 --> 01:04:54.226
they always say the same thing.

01:04:55.726 --> 01:04:58.126
"If it weren't for Ju Ah,"

01:04:58.566 --> 01:05:00.736
"I never would've married you."

01:05:03.136 --> 01:05:05.266
Ever since I was a little kid.

01:05:06.006 --> 01:05:08.976
even if I pulled the covers over my head...

01:05:09.276 --> 01:05:11.546
and plugged my ears as tight as I could,

01:05:12.616 --> 01:05:13.846
those words...

01:05:14.246 --> 01:05:18.116
would pierce through the covers, through my ears,

01:05:19.656 --> 01:05:22.086
and stab me right in the heart.

01:05:26.656 --> 01:05:30.066
(Gaetdali Beach)

01:05:36.666 --> 01:05:39.406
Gosh, what is she doing now, worrying me like this?

01:05:41.836 --> 01:05:42.846
No, wait.

01:05:43.676 --> 01:05:45.306
She asked me to pretend I don't know anything.

01:05:47.746 --> 01:05:48.876
I...

01:05:50.016 --> 01:05:52.456
often felt like I was someone...

01:05:52.956 --> 01:05:56.156
who wasn't needed in this world.

01:05:58.126 --> 01:05:59.996
My existence...

01:06:01.126 --> 01:06:06.066
wasn't the fruit of their love, but just a mistake!

01:06:08.796 --> 01:06:10.006
It was like...

01:06:10.966 --> 01:06:15.006
I've spent my whole life feeling abandoned, I guess?

01:06:40.736 --> 01:06:43.206
- Stop drinking, honey. - Leave me alone.

01:06:46.406 --> 01:06:48.076
What are you so mad about?

01:06:48.706 --> 01:06:49.876
We'll talk later.

01:06:50.546 --> 01:06:51.706
Is something wrong?

01:06:52.476 --> 01:06:53.476
No, it's nothing.

01:06:53.976 --> 01:06:57.286
What is wrong with you, honey? You're the one who said to be late.

01:06:57.346 --> 01:06:58.946
Just shut up already.

01:07:00.556 --> 01:07:01.556
Uncle.

01:07:04.456 --> 01:07:08.726
You promised you'd treat me well around your family if we moved in.

01:07:09.166 --> 01:07:11.726
When we gave your brother the deposit to move in here,

01:07:12.436 --> 01:07:14.396
that one promise was all I had to go on.

01:07:15.466 --> 01:07:16.466
Hui Gyeong.

01:07:17.266 --> 01:07:20.076
I am truly sorry about that.

01:07:21.876 --> 01:07:24.576
- I'll get the money quickly and... - Seong Mi.

01:07:26.016 --> 01:07:27.376
If this is too hard for you,

01:07:28.416 --> 01:07:30.046
you don't have to stay with me.

01:07:33.216 --> 01:07:34.216
What?

01:07:35.386 --> 01:07:37.526
- Dad? - Hey.

01:07:37.586 --> 01:07:38.686
I'm sorry, Mom.

01:07:39.826 --> 01:07:40.896
Seong Mi and I...

01:07:41.756 --> 01:07:43.026
We're splitting up.

01:07:56.706 --> 01:07:58.906
(Special thanks to Go Myung Hwan, Jo Seung Je, and Eom Ji In)

01:08:22.766 --> 01:08:25.466
(Recipe for Love)

01:08:25.566 --> 01:08:28.176
I wish I'd never been born...

01:08:28.306 --> 01:08:29.306
Hey!

01:08:29.306 --> 01:08:31.846
Her husband blew all their money, so she's living with her family.

01:08:33.016 --> 01:08:36.016
When your daughter's struggling, shouldn't you be there for her?

01:08:36.146 --> 01:08:39.146
You're the one who messed up. Why are you taking it out on me?

01:08:39.386 --> 01:08:41.056
- Should I do it here? - Do what?

01:08:41.116 --> 01:08:44.056
- Didn't you want my autograph? - Gosh, how conceited.

01:08:44.126 --> 01:08:47.296
- I heard that. - When did you go to Seoul? A hotel?

01:08:47.796 --> 01:08:49.666
The more I think, this is crazy.

01:08:49.766 --> 01:08:51.296
Are you really getting a divorce?